Definition: a feeling of profound respect for someone or something
Example: the fear of God; the Chinese reverence for the dead; the French treat food with gentle reverence; his respect for the law bordered on veneration
Synonyms: verb, emotion, reverence, adj, all, reverent, reverential, pious, revere, awe, veneration, venerate, a, feeling, of, profound, respect, for, someone, or, something, the, God, Chinese, dead, French, treat, food, with, gentle, his, law, bordered, on
Category: noun.feeling
